								Astro
							</a>
							<a href="https://svelte.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="stack-chip">
								<img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/svelte/FF3E00" width="14" height="14" alt="Svelte" />
								Svelte
							</a>
							<a href="https://tailwindcss.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="stack-chip">
								<img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/tailwindcss/06B6D4" width="14" height="14" alt="Tailwind CSS" />
								Tailwind CSS
							</a>
							<a href="https://daisyui.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="stack-chip">
								<img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/daisyui/5A0EF8" width="14" height="14" alt="DaisyUI" />
								DaisyUI
							</a>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="about-projects">
						<p class="about-projects-label" data-i18n="about.projects">More projects</p>
						<div class="about-projects-grid">
							<a href="https://teslagear.crstian.me/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="project-btn">
								<img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/tesla/CC0000" width="14" height="14" alt="Tesla" />
								Tesla Gear
							</a>
							<a href="https://github.com/crstian19/teslamate-achievements" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="project-btn">
								<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.477 2 12c0 4.418 2.865 8.166 6.839 9.489.5.092.682-.217.682-.482 0-.237-.009-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.604-3.369-1.341-3.369-1.341-.454-1.154-1.11-1.462-1.11-1.462-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.03 1.531 1.03.892 1.529 2.341 1.087 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.11-4.555-4.943 0-1.091.39-1.984 1.029-2.683-.103-.253-.446-1.27.098-2.647 0 0 .84-.269 2.75 1.025A9.564 9.564 0 0 1 12 6.844a9.59 9.59 0 0 1 2.504.337c1.909-1.294 2.747-1.025 2.747-1.025.546 1.377.202 2.394.1 2.647.64.699 1.028 1.592 1.028 2.683 0 3.842-2.339 4.687-4.566 4.935.359.309.678.919.678 1.852 0 1.336-.012 2.415-.012 2.741 0 .267.18.578.688.48C19.138 20.163 22 16.418 22 12c0-5.523-4.477-10-10-10z"/></svg>
								TeslaMate Achievements
							</a>
							<span class="project-btn project-btn--soon">
								<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
								SentryHub
								<span class="project-soon-badge" data-i18n="about.soon">Soon</span>
							</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- FAQ Modal -->
			<div class="modal-overlay" id="modal-faq" aria-hidden="true" inert>
				<div class="modal-box" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="faq-title">
					<button class="modal-close" data-close="modal-faq" aria-label="Close">&times;</button>
					<h2 id="faq-title" class="modal-title" data-i18n="faq.title">FAQ</h2>
					<dl class="faq-list">
						<dt data-i18n="faq.q1">What is Tesdash?</dt>
						<dd data-i18n-html="faq.a1">Tesdash is a dashboard that lets you launch streaming services, music, sports, and other apps directly from your Tesla's browser — all opening in fullscreen with a single tap.</dd>

						<dt data-i18n="faq.q2">How do I open an app?</dt>
						<dd data-i18n-html="faq.a2">Just tap or click any app card. It will open the service in a new fullscreen tab in your Tesla's browser.</dd>

						<dt data-i18n="faq.q3">What is the URL Launcher?</dt>
						<dd data-i18n-html="faq.a3">The bar at the top of the page lets you type any URL and open it — handy for sites not listed in the dashboard.</dd>

						<dt data-i18n="faq.q4">Can I reorder the categories?</dt>
						<dd data-i18n-html="faq.a4">Yes. Grab the dotted handle to the left of any category name and drag it to a new position. Your order is remembered across visits.</dd>

						<dt data-i18n="faq.q5">Does it work outside my Tesla?</dt>
						<dd data-i18n-html="faq.a5">Yes, Tesdash works in any modern browser on any device. The fullscreen behavior is optimized for Tesla's in-vehicle browser.</dd>

						<dt data-i18n="faq.q6">Is it free?</dt>
						<dd data-i18n-html="faq.a6">Completely free, no account or sign-up required.</dd>

						<dt data-i18n="faq.q7">Does Tesdash store any of my data?</dt>
						<dd data-i18n-html="faq.a7">No. The only data saved locally is your category order, language preference, country filter, and any custom apps you have added. Nothing is ever sent to a server.</dd>

						<dt data-i18n="faq.q8">How do I change the language?</dt>
						<dd data-i18n-html="faq.a8">Tap the language button in the top-right corner to open the Language &amp; Region settings. From there you can choose the interface language and filter apps by country.</dd>

						<dt data-i18n="faq.q9">What does the country filter do?</dt>
						<dd data-i18n-html="faq.a9">It hides apps that are not available in your country, such as regional charging networks. Your country is detected automatically from your car's timezone, or you can set it manually in the Language &amp; Region settings.</dd>

						<dt data-i18n="faq.q10">Can I add my own apps?</dt>
						<dd data-i18n-html="faq.a10">Yes. Tap the + button in the bottom-right corner to open the Add App form. Enter a name, URL, logo, category and color. You can also choose whether the app opens in fullscreen or in a normal tab.</dd>

						<dt data-i18n="faq.q11">Can an app open without fullscreen?</dt>
						<dd data-i18n-html="faq.a11">Yes. When adding a custom app via the + button, toggle off Fullscreen to open it directly in the browser. Self-hosted users can also set <code>fullscreen: false</code> on any app in <code>config.yml</code>.</dd>
					</dl>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Self-Host Modal -->
			<div class="modal-overlay" id="modal-selfhost" aria-hidden="true" inert>
				<div class="modal-box" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="selfhost-title">
					<button class="modal-close" data-close="modal-selfhost" aria-label="Close">&times;</button>
					<h2 id="selfhost-title" class="modal-title" data-i18n="selfhost.title">Self-Hosting</h2>
					<div class="selfhost-content">
						<p class="selfhost-desc" data-i18n="selfhost.desc">Tesdash is open source and fully self-hostable. Find setup instructions, configuration options, and more on the GitHub repository.</p>
						<a href="https://github.com/crstian19/tesdash" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="selfhost-github-btn">
							<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.477 2 12c0 4.418 2.865 8.166 6.839 9.489.5.092.682-.217.682-.482 0-.237-.009-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.604-3.369-1.341-3.369-1.341-.454-1.154-1.11-1.462-1.11-1.462-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.03 1.531 1.03.892 1.529 2.341 1.087 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.11-4.555-4.943 0-1.091.39-1.984 1.029-2.683-.103-.253-.446-1.27.098-2.647 0 0 .84-.269 2.75 1.025A9.564 9.564 0 0 1 12 6.844a9.59 9.59 0 0 1 2.504.337c1.909-1.294 2.747-1.025 2.747-1.025.546 1.377.202 2.394.1 2.647.64.699 1.028 1.592 1.028 2.683 0 3.842-2.339 4.687-4.566 4.935.359.309.678.919.678 1.852 0 1.336-.012 2.415-.012 2.741 0 .267.18.578.688.48C19.138 20.163 22 16.418 22 12c0-5.523-4.477-10-10-10z"/></svg>
							GitHub
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Charging Calculator Modal -->
			<div class="modal-overlay" id="modal-charger" aria-hidden="true" inert>
				<div class="modal-box" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="charger-title">
					<button class="modal-close" data-close="modal-charger" aria-label="Close">&times;</button>
					<h2 id="charger-title" class="modal-title charger-modal-title">
						<svg class="charger-bolt" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true" width="20" height="20">
							<path d="M13 2L3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z" fill="#facc15" stroke="#facc15" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
							<path class="bolt-trace" d="M13 2L3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z" fill="none" stroke="white" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" pathLength="100"/>
						</svg>
						EV Charging Calculator
					</h2>
					<div class="form-row" style="margin-bottom:1rem">
						<label class="form-label" for="ch-model">Tesla Model</label>
						<select class="form-input form-select" id="ch-model">
							<option value="">— Custom —</option>
							<optgroup label="Model 3 (pre-Highland)">
								<option value="57.5">Model 3 RWD — 57.5 kWh net</option>
								<option value="75">Model 3 Long Range AWD — 75 kWh net</option>
								<option value="75">Model 3 Performance — 75 kWh net</option>
							</optgroup>
							<optgroup label="Model 3 Highland (2024+)">
								<option value="57.5">Model 3 Highland RWD — 57.5 kWh net</option>
								<option value="75">Model 3 Highland Long Range AWD — 75 kWh net</option>
								<option value="75">Model 3 Highland Performance — 75 kWh net</option>
							</optgroup>
							<optgroup label="Model Y (pre-Juniper)">
								<option value="57.5">Model Y RWD — 57.5 kWh net</option>
								<option value="75">Model Y Long Range AWD — 75 kWh net</option>
								<option value="75">Model Y Performance — 75 kWh net</option>
							</optgroup>
							<optgroup label="Model Y Juniper (2025+)">
								<option value="57.5">Model Y Juniper RWD — 57.5 kWh net</option>
								<option value="75">Model Y Juniper Long Range AWD — 75 kWh net</option>
								<option value="75">Model Y Juniper Performance — 75 kWh net</option>
							</optgroup>
							<optgroup label="Model S">
								<option value="95">Model S Long Range — 95 kWh net</option>
								<option value="95">Model S Plaid — 95 kWh net</option>
							</optgroup>
							<optgroup label="Model X">
								<option value="95">Model X Long Range — 95 kWh net</option>
								<option value="95">Model X Plaid — 95 kWh net</option>
							</optgroup>
							<optgroup label="Cybertruck">
								<option value="108">Cybertruck Standard Range — 108 kWh net</option>
								<option value="119">Cybertruck Long Range — 119 kWh net</option>
								<option value="119">Cybertruck Cyberbeast — 119 kWh net</option>
							</optgroup>
						</select>
					</div>
					<div class="charger-grid">
						<div class="charger-field">
							<label class="form-label" for="ch-capacity">Battery Capacity</label>
							<div class="charger-input-wrap">
								<input class="form-input" type="number" id="ch-capacity" value="75" min="1" max="300" step="0.5" />
								<span class="charger-unit">kWh</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="charger-field">
							<label class="form-label" for="ch-power">Charging Power</label>
							<div class="charger-input-wrap">
								<input class="form-input" type="number" id="ch-power" value="11" min="1" max="350" step="0.5" />
								<span class="charger-unit">kW</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="charger-field">
							<label class="form-label" for="ch-price">Price</label>
							<div class="charger-input-wrap">
								<input class="form-input" type="number" id="ch-price" value="0.20" min="0" max="10" step="0.01" />
								<span class="charger-unit">€/kWh</span>
							</div>
